g.title: observations_table
g.text: # Descripion: table defining elements in main observations table
Unique ID for report (unique ID given by combination of
e.g. GRUAN station name, ship name, site name etc

Structure upon which sensor is mounted, e.g. ship, drifting buoy,

Accuracy to which height of station known (m)

Report duration (s), e.g. 86400 = daily obs, 3600 hourly
Precision to which time was recorded (s)
Reference Time (e.g. referenced to time server, atomic clock, radio

ID for profile data or missing (NULL) otherwise.

values for above surface (e.g. sondes), negative for below (e.g.
xbt). For visual observations, height of the visual observing platform.
Reporting precision of observation in units given by 'Units' variable.
Method of estimating the standard uncertainty

Uncertainty due to errors in the observations that are correlated

Whether the exposure of the instrument will impact on the

Whether observation can be traced to international standards.
